VIRAL GASTROENTERITIS UPDATE 2003 (05)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[Please note that reports in these updates have been edited to replace
"flu-like", "Norwalk-like", "bug", etc, with the International Committee on
Taxonomy of Viruses approved designation "Norovirus" for the calicivirus
presumed or confirmed to be responsible for sudden onset viral
gastroenteritis. - Mod.CP]
In this update:
[1] Hospitals & schools (Scotland - Aberdeen)
[2] Nursing homes (USA - Michigan)
[3] & [4] Cruise ship (USA - Hawaii)
