Date: Wed 5 Feb 2003
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: Melbourne Herald Sun (Australia), Wed 5 Feb 2003 [edited]
<http://www.heraldsun.news.com.au/common/story_page/0,5478,5940297%255E401,00.html>

USA: Norovirus outbreak on Hawaiian cruise
------------------------------------------
An outbreak of viral infections similar to those that hit cruise ships in
the Caribbean and Alaska cut short a Hawaiian cruise after nearly 300
passengers and crew members became sick. 10 days into the 15 day voyage
from Los Angeles to 4 Hawaiian islands, Princess Cruises diverted the Sun
Princess to Honolulu so nearly 2000 passengers could take flights home.
About 100 passengers, about half of whom were sick, stayed with the ship as
it left yesterday for Los Angeles, Princess Cruises spokesman Tom Dow said.
He noted that the cruise appeals to some people who are wary of air travel.
Most people who contracted suspected norovirus infection recovered before
the end of the voyage, cruise officials said. After 4 new cases were
reported on Monday, the cruise line, in consultation with health officials,
decided to divert the ship, Dow said. All crew stayed aboard, along with a
team sanitising the ship.
